Persian Gulf Stocks: Kuwait’s Zain and Zain Saudi Arabia

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-27T09:41:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/persian-gulf-stocks-kuwait-s-zain-and-zain-saudi-arabia.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated
for a fourth day, losing less than 0.1 percent at 1:04 p.m. in
emirate.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  declined 0.5 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.  Mobile Telecommunications Co. (ZAIN KK) headed for the
biggest drop since June 2, losing 1.9 percent to 1,020 fils. The
Kuwaiti phone company known as Zain had its price estimate cut
15 percent to 1.04 dinars at Nomura Holdings Inc.  Mobile Telecommunications Co. of  Saudi Arabia  (ZAINKSA AB)
fell for the first time in three days, losing 1.4 percent to
6.85 riyals. The unit of Kuwait’s Zain had its price estimate
lowered to 8.2 riyals from 9.3 riyals at Nomura.  To contact the reporter on this story:
